# HealthSync AI Assistant — Model Training Plan

## Current State

Your AI assistant ([ai_service.py](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/HealthSys/HealthSync-Comprehensive/backend/utils/ai_service.py)) currently uses:
- **Groq API** (LLaMA 3.3 70B) or **OpenAI** as external LLM providers
- **Rule-based fallbacks** when no API key is configured
- **Hardcoded knowledge base** for drug interactions (only 4 drugs), vital ranges, and care protocols (only 3 conditions)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The current system is NOT trained — it relies on generic LLM prompts and static lookup tables. This plan will make each feature significantly more accurate and clinically relevant.

---

## Strategy Overview: Hybrid Architecture

Rather than training a single monolithic model, I recommend a **hybrid approach** — the right tool for each job:

| Feature | Approach | Why |
|---------|----------|-----|
| **Care Notes AI** | Fine-tuned LLM (Mistral 7B or LLaMA 3.1 8B) | Requires natural language generation with medical terminology |
| **Recommendations** | RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) + Fine-tuned LLM | Needs access to clinical guidelines + patient context |
| **Risk Analysis** | Gradient Boosted Trees (XGBoost/LightGBM) | Tabular patient data → risk score is a classic ML classification task |
| **Drug Interactions** | Knowledge Graph + NER model | Structured relational data; lookup + severity classification |
| **Vital Analysis** | Time-series anomaly detection (LSTM/Isolation Forest) | Sequential vital sign data → trend detection |

