## Feature 1: Care Notes AI

### Model
**Mistral 7B Instruct** (fine-tuned) or **BioMistral 7B**
- Small enough to run locally on a GPU with 16GB VRAM, or deploy on RunPod/Lambda
- BioMistral is already pre-trained on biomedical text

### Datasets

| Dataset | Source | Size | License |
|---------|--------|------|---------|
| **MIMIC-III Clinical Notes** | [PhysioNet](https://physionet.org/content/mimiciii/1.4/) | ~2M notes | PhysioNet Credentialed (free, requires application) |
| **MIMIC-IV Discharge Summaries** | [PhysioNet](https://physionet.org/content/mimic-iv-note/2.2/) | ~330K notes | PhysioNet Credentialed |
| **i2b2 Clinical NLP Datasets** | [DBMI Portal](https://portal.dbmi.hms.harvard.edu/) | ~1K annotated notes | DUA required |
| **PMC-Patients** | [HuggingFace](https://huggingface.co/datasets/zhengyun21/PMC-Patients) | ~167K patient summaries | Open |
| **MedText** | [HuggingFace](https://huggingface.co/datasets/BI55/MedText) | Clinical text samples | Open |

### Training Approach
1. **Get MIMIC-III access** (takes 1-2 weeks — sign DUA on PhysioNet, complete CITI training)
2. Extract `NOTEEVENTS` table → filter for nursing care notes, discharge summaries
3. Create instruction-tuning pairs: `{input: patient_vitals + context, output: clinical_note}`
4. Fine-tune with **QLoRA** (4-bit quantization) using `transformers` + `peft` + `trl`
5. ~5,000-10,000 high-quality pairs is sufficient for fine-tuning

### Hardware
- **Training**: 1x NVIDIA A100 40GB (or 2x RTX 4090) — ~$1-2/hr on RunPod/Lambda
- **Inference**: Can run on CPU with GGUF quantization via `llama.cpp`, or 1x RTX 3090

