## Feature 2: AI Recommendations (RAG)

### Model
**RAG Pipeline**: Embedding model + Vector DB + Fine-tuned LLM

| Component | Tool |
|-----------|------|
| Embeddings | `all-MiniLM-L6-v2` (384-dim, fast) or `BioLORD-2023-M` (biomedical) |
| Vector Store | ChromaDB (local, lightweight) or FAISS |
| Generator LLM | Same Mistral 7B from Feature 1 |

### Datasets (Knowledge Base for RAG)

| Dataset | Source | Description |
|---------|--------|-------------|
| **ClinicalGuidelines.gov** | [guidelines.gov archive](https://www.ahrq.gov/gam/index.html) | AHRQ clinical practice guidelines |
| **UpToDate-like Summaries** | [WikiDoc](https://www.wikidoc.org/) | Open medical wiki with treatment guidelines |
| **OpenGuidelines** | [GitHub](https://github.com/openmedx/guidelines) | Community medical guidelines |
| **PubMedQA** | [HuggingFace](https://huggingface.co/datasets/qiaojin/PubMedQA) | ~273K biomedical QA pairs |
| **MedQuAD** | [GitHub](https://github.com/abachaa/MedQuAD) | ~47K medical QA pairs from NIH |
| **Home Care Best Practices** | CMS / Medicare Conditions of Participation | Home health care protocols |

### Training Approach
1. **Chunk** clinical guidelines into ~512-token passages
2. **Embed** using BioLORD-2023-M and store in ChromaDB
3. At query time: retrieve top-5 relevant chunks → inject into LLM prompt
4. Fine-tune the generator LLM on `{question + retrieved_context → recommendation}` pairs
5. No MIMIC access needed — public guidelines are sufficient

