## Feature 3: Risk Analysis

### Model
**XGBoost** or **LightGBM** (gradient boosted decision trees)
- Best for tabular patient data
- Interpretable (feature importance = explainable risk factors)
- Fast inference, no GPU needed

### Datasets

| Dataset | Source | Features |
|---------|--------|----------|
| **MIMIC-III / MIMIC-IV** | [PhysioNet](https://physionet.org/content/mimiciii/1.4/) | Patient demographics, vitals, labs, outcomes |
| **eICU Collaborative Research Database** | [PhysioNet](https://physionet.org/content/eicu-crd/2.0/) | 200K+ ICU stays with outcomes |
| **Heart Failure Clinical Records** | [UCI ML Repo](https://archive.ics.uci.edu/dataset/519/heart+failure+clinical+records+dataset) | 299 patients, 13 features |
| **Diabetes 130-US Hospitals** | [UCI ML Repo](https://archive.ics.uci.edu/dataset/296/diabetes+130+us+hospitals+for+years+1999+2008) | 100K+ patient records |
| **Home Healthcare Readmission** | [CMS OASIS Dataset](https://www.cms.gov/Medicare/Quality-Initiatives-Patient-Assessment-Instruments/HomeHealthQualityInits) | Home health patient outcomes |
| **Framingham Heart Study** | [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/dileep070/heart-disease-prediction-using-logistic-regression) | Cardiovascular risk prediction |

### Training Approach
1. **Feature engineering** from patient data:
   - Demographics (age, gender, BMI)
   - Vital sign trends (rolling averages, variance)
   - Medication adherence rate
   - Number of ADL deficits
   - Comorbidity count (Charlson index)
   - Days since last hospital visit
   - Fall history count
2. **Target variable**: Risk level (low/moderate/high) or readmission within 30 days
3. Train XGBoost with 5-fold cross-validation
4. Export model with `joblib` → load in your existing [ml_agent.py](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/HealthSys/HealthSync-Comprehensive/backend/agents/ml_agent.py)

### Code Integration
