## Feature 4: Drug Interactions

### Model
**Knowledge Graph** + optional **NER model** for medication extraction

### Datasets

| Dataset | Source | Size | Format |
|---------|--------|------|--------|
| **DrugBank** | [drugbank.com](https://go.drugbank.com/releases/latest) | 14,000+ drugs, 300K+ interactions | XML (free academic license) |
| **RxNorm** | [NLM/NIH](https://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm/index.html) | Standard drug nomenclature | RRF files (free UMLS license) |
| **DDI Corpus** | [GitHub](https://github.com/isegura/DDICorpus) | 1,017 texts, 5,021 DDI annotations | XML (NER training) |
| **TWOSIDES** | [tatonettilab.org](http://tatonetti-lab.org/resources/tatonetti-stm.html) | 868 drugs, 1,318 side effects | CSV |
| **FDA Adverse Event Reporting (FAERS)** | [FDA](https://open.fda.gov/data/faers/) | Millions of adverse events | JSON API |
| **NDF-RT (Drug Interactions)** | [NLM](https://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/sourcereleasedocs/current/NDFRT/) | Structured drug-drug interactions | UMLS |

### Training Approach
1. **Download DrugBank XML** (apply for academic license — approved in 1-3 days)
2. Parse `<drug-interactions>` elements → build interaction database
3. Store in SQLite table: `drug_a, drug_b, severity, description, mechanism`
4. Replace your current 4-drug hardcoded dictionary with **14,000+ drugs**
5. **(Optional)** Train a **BioBERT NER model** on DDI Corpus to extract drug names from free-text clinical notes
6. **(Optional)** Use FAERS data to add real-world severity scoring

### Code Integration
```python
# Replace hardcoded dict in ai_service.py with:
def check_drug_interactions(self, medications):
    interactions = []
    for i, drug_a in enumerate(medications):
        for drug_b in medications[i+1:]:
            result = db.query(
                "SELECT * FROM drug_interactions WHERE drug_a=? AND drug_b=?",
                [normalize(drug_a), normalize(drug_b)]
            )
            if result:
                interactions.append(result)
    return interactions
```

