## Feature 5: Vital Analysis

### Model
**Isolation Forest** (anomaly detection) + **LSTM** (trend prediction)

### Datasets

| Dataset | Source | Description |
|---------|--------|-------------|
| **MIMIC-III Waveform Database** | [PhysioNet](https://physionet.org/content/mimic3wdb/1.0/) | Continuous vital sign waveforms |
| **MIMIC-IV (vitalsign table)** | [PhysioNet](https://physionet.org/content/mimic-iv/2.2/) | Structured vital readings |
| **eICU Vital Signs** | [PhysioNet](https://physionet.org/content/eicu-crd/2.0/) | Periodic vital measurements |
| **VitalDB** | [vitaldb.net](https://vitaldb.net/) | 6,388 surgical cases with continuous vitals |
| **UCR Time Series Archive** | [UCR](https://www.cs.ucr.edu/~eamonn/time_series_data_2018/) | Benchmark time series datasets |

### Training Approach

#### Anomaly Detection (Isolation Forest)
1. Train on normal vital ranges from MIMIC-IV
2. Features: heart_rate, systolic_bp, diastolic_bp, spo2, temperature, respiratory_rate
3. Model flags readings that deviate from learned normal patterns
4. Much better than your current static threshold approach

#### Trend Prediction (LSTM)
1. Build sequences: `[vital_t-5, vital_t-4, ..., vital_t] → vital_t+1`
2. Train on MIMIC waveform data or periodic vitals
3. Predict next-hour vitals → flag if predicted values enter danger zone
4. Enables **proactive alerts** before vitals actually become critical

```python
# Enhanced vital analysis
from sklearn.ensemble import IsolationForest
anomaly_detector = IsolationForest(contamination=0.05)
anomaly_detector.fit(training_vitals)
is_anomaly = anomaly_detector.predict(new_vitals)  # -1 = anomaly
```

