## Phased Implementation Roadmap

### Phase A: Quick Wins (Week 1-2) — No Training Required
- [ ] **Drug Interactions**: Download DrugBank → parse XML → populate SQLite table → replace hardcoded 4-drug dictionary with 14,000+ drugs
- [ ] **RAG Setup**: Chunk clinical guidelines → embed with BioLORD → store in ChromaDB → enhance recommendations with retrieved context
- [ ] **Vital Analysis**: Train Isolation Forest on existing patient data or MIMIC vitals (< 1 hour to train)

### Phase B: ML Models (Week 3-4)
- [ ] **Risk Analysis**: Feature engineer from your existing database → train XGBoost → deploy as `risk_xgboost.pkl`
- [ ] **Vital Trend Prediction**: Train LSTM on vital time-series data
- [ ] Apply for MIMIC-III/IV PhysioNet access (if not already done)

### Phase C: LLM Fine-Tuning (Week 5-8)
- [ ] Get MIMIC access approved
- [ ] Extract and clean clinical notes
- [ ] Create instruction-tuning dataset (~5-10K pairs)
- [ ] Fine-tune BioMistral 7B with QLoRA
- [ ] Deploy locally with `llama.cpp` or `vLLM`
- [ ] Replace Groq/OpenAI API dependency with local model

